If these what- ifer's predict the sun coming out tomorrow, the sun would explode in a fiery -- well, it is a fiery ball -- in a non-fiery ball.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Emily --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: How was that?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: You were going good -- you were going good.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I think that -- I believe that Webster's will add what-ifer's to the dictionary.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: What-ifer's.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: What the ifer's.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAM
utterances.utterance: Now you went over the line. You went over the line.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Now, Emily, you know, one of the things that happens before a hearing like this as you can imagine, all the lawyers, all the staff that works for the congressional leadership, and all the lawyers who work for the, now, people who have to get a lawyer because now they have to go testify in front of them, what are they going to do this weekend to really see if they can make it not boring, as Jesse was suggesting?

utterances.speaker: COMPAGNO
utterances.utterance: Hopefully they will be doing as much research and thorough preparation as possible on both sides anticipating the questions. I think it's really telling and kind of humorous that the attorney for the whistleblower who sent that cease and desist letter to the White House, how he literally was, like -- I mean, it was like theatrical. Anyone who is complicit in this vindictive this campaign, action or inaction, morally and legally responsible, I mean, I feel like he would give anything to be the whistleblower himself. But I also think that the trailer for next week was the Kavanaugh hearings for the Democrats. And that their pattern is they are totally soaked for the opportunity to grandstand and saying next week is going to be lit. But really, we are just going to hear the same things that already occurred in private testimony that was leaked out with no bombshells, even though they were telling us there were bombshells.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I can't think of anybody in recent congressional testimony that has enhanced their reputation. Do you remember?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Oliver North.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: I was going to say,

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Oliver North.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Well, I said in recent history.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: We're in our 70s.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: By the way, Dana, how come you didn't pick up on Emily saying lit?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Why, because that's just like hip language.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: That's very hip language and Jesse --

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: OK, Boomer.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: -- Jesse, that is dramatic, it's going to be lit. That's next week, it's going to be lit.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: That's right. They need some drama for sure.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: And what we need is a mom text about his monologue at the beginning because I can't --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: That's coming.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: All right, up next, is the Democratic field about to be thrown into disarray? Billionaire Michael Bloomberg is eyeing to run that could end up and upend the entire field.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: New signs 2020 Democrats are heading for a disaster. The party is now so radical that billionaire Mike Bloomberg is thinking about jumping into the race. And it looks like swing state voters agree with Mike. A new poll says 55 percent of them prefer a moderate candidate. But liberal contenders are doubling down and proving just how extreme they really are. Bernie Sanders just unveiled his far left immigration plan while Liza Warren continues to flaunt her outrageous wealth tax. But no one is more excited for Bloomberg to enter the race than President Trump. Listen.

utterances.speaker: TRUMP
utterances.utterance: He's not going to do well, but I think he's going to hurt Biden actually. But he doesn't have the magic to do well. Little Michael will fail. He'll spend a lot of money. He's got some really big issues, he's got some personal problems, and he's got a lot of other problems. There is nobody I'd rather run against them little Michael, that I could tell you.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Little Michael, Dana. What he said about the magic that's lacking, I would agree with.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Charisma, right?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: He doesn't really light it up out there.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: When somebody walks in the room and they want to be a leader, they should be able to be somebody that's everyone turns their head and says, oh, who is that in the room. Maybe Michael Bloomberg has that. I've never been -- I haven't actually into many rooms with him.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Really?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: No, I have not. I don't know what President Trump was referring to in regards to personal problems. He just sort of throws that out there like --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: What was that?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I don't know what he meant, but you know, maybe we'll find out.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: -- I think we should find out.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: You know what, let's call the Ukrainian president.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Yes, he'll help us.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: But I think that -- I think Bloomberg has been convinced that Biden's candidacy is doomed, because remember Biden said I won't -- Bloomberg said I will not get in the race if Biden does. And Biden got in late, he waited until April. And as soon as he did, Bloomberg said, OK, I'm not going to run. So, something had to have changed in his mind that he thinks Biden's not going to make it and Elizabeth Warren is going to destroy our chances of beating President Trump. I alone can fix it and so that's why --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: But so, he is the fresh new face and he is also 78? So you have Joe, you have Bernie, you have --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Warren.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Michael Blooomberg, Liz -- its grumpy old man plus Mrs. Doubtfire. I mean, I hear they're going to like -- you're going to like enter a giant Redwood tree into the race so they appear younger.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: And they're all from the northeast. It's just, you know --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Like Galapagos turtle, would be nice.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Hey wait a minute, wait a minute. Doesn't it all apply to Trump, everything you just said? He's 70s from the northeast.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: He's ageless.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Oh, he's ageless.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: He's not grumpy.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: He's like a beautiful stone.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Unlimited wisdom.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: That's one --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: His unlimited wisdom and guidance. Yes, I forgot about that.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: So, what do you think about Bloomberg? What does that signal to you, Juan Williams?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Well, first of all, let me just say this. I don't think this is anything but the Democratic primary process playing out as I recall last time you had. By the way, do you think Marco Rubio should be jealous? Little Michael? What happened to little Marco?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I'd be glad. I'd be glad. I'd be like (inaudible).

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Enough, right?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: All right. Because, I mean, you know, I mean last time it was pretty rough among the Republican. Little Marco, Lying Ted, do you want to see that phase, you know, Carly -- all that stuff. Anyway, so I think that, you know, Bloomberg to Greg's point, is a disruptor because I think it's a shot at Biden and David Axelrod who ran Obama's campaign said today that he thought, you know, this is a vote of no confidence coming from Bloomberg directed, targeted at Biden. The second part of that is the money issue because Biden's been struggling with money and Bloomberg obviously has unlimited money.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Right.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: And Wall Street this week, I think one of the untold stories this week, is Wall Street has just been going bananas over the idea that Liz Warren might beat Biden and she'll come in and she was going to go after Wall Street. So I think that's all what we are seeing here. But I do want to just remind you guys that in terms of the populous spirit of America, on the left and the right, right now, I just don't think any billionaire is going to do all that well. This is the second billionaire, Tom Steyer and now Michael Bloomberg in the Democratic race. And I just think all the energy is about, oh, you know what, the rich pay more taxes? Good idea. OH, the rich aren't -- why is the system rigged for the rich?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Joe Biden had some words for the entry into the race by Michael Bloomberg. Let's watch that.

utterances.speaker: JOE BIDEN, D-PRESIDENTIAL CANDIDATE
utterances.utterance: They're welcome in the race. Michael is a solid guy. And let's see where it goes. I have no problem with him getting in the race. And in terms of he's running because of me? Last polls I looked at, I'm pretty far ahead.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: That's true.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: What do you think about that?

utterances.speaker: COMPAGNO
utterances.utterance: Yes. Well, he's playing it safe and we heard just before this, you know, he's walked back some comments about Elizabeth Warren too. I think what it shows is the disconnect and how broad of a chasm there is between donor Democrats and the rest of the Democratic Party. I think Bloomberg is no match for a strong Biden, but he is for a weak Biden because first of all, Biden has the people of color vote, that there is no way that Bloomberg can try to get obviously. But at this point, with that aside, the cash on hand issue, the person who has the most to lose at this point tonight is Mayor Pete to me because he's the one that kind of had positioned himself in that lane of more of the moderate making sense type Democrat, right? Not spending $52 trillion on things. I also think what's interesting; the Gallup poll last month that came out had said 75 percent of voters are satisfied with their Democratic candidates. And the last time we had a number that was anywhere near that close was 2007 when Obama, Clinton, and John Edwards were running. And up until now, the numbers have been abysmal.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Yes. I wonder if John Edwards is thinking about jumping into the race.

utterances.speaker: COMPAGNO
utterances.utterance: Right? I mean --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Also this week, Kamala Harris made some news for I guess some -- for good reasons this time and maybe Greg has some thoughts on that. Let's hear Kamala.

utterances.speaker: SEN. KAMALA HARRIS, D-CALIF.
utterances.utterance: He's selling us out. He's selling out our system of justice, not to mention that he has sold out working people and sold out our value. It's really is -- it's fascinating. If it weren't so troubling it would be really incredibly fascinating. And these are those moments where I really wish that I had taken more psychology classes.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: So, she's dialed into a Trump rally right there.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Right.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: She's all wired up and has the headphones on, Greg. What do you think?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: You know, her entire persona is, "I just can't." And the fact is you have to be able to respond and counter that person. She is like working the counter at the DMV 15 minutes before the end of her shift and she is looking at the clock and cracking jokes to her friends while you're still in line.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: She's like, oh, god, I just, you know, I can't be bothered. And the fact is you have to be bothered. You have to. And I wonder if she's actually really competed in anything because it doesn't seem like she likes to compete.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: That's a great point. You have to reach out and take the nomination.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: And I don't think she wants it that badly. And you look at her and to your point about -- it looks like she thinks everybody agrees with her, like she's just in a bubble in San Francisco.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: It's kind of hard to imagine that the Democrats are mad at Facebook for not policing ads or like having ads at all because how else could you get a very poorly produced --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: -- totally cheap ad like that and get --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Wait a minute? That was an ad?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: That was an ad.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: That was an ad?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Oh, I thought she was screaming at --

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: That was a Facebook ad.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: That was the worst ad I've ever seen. I didn't know that was an ad. I thought it was like a Beto like, you know --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: That was an ad.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: -- watch me watch a Trump rally everybody.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: All right. All right. I have question for you, Jessie.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: What?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Can Bloomberg -- if Bloomberg did win, could beat Trump?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: No.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: I think --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: He can't win and he can't beat Trump.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Well, I don't know --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I think you maybe because you live New York right now. You have and outside view of Michael Bloomberg.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: OK.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: The rest of the country doesn't know him, doesn't care that much about him. And everything they've heard about him, they haven't heard good things. They've heard he wants to take your big goal.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Oh, on thing -- I would say the one -- that might be true, although if you were looking at -- if you're a Democratic operative and you have been receiving lots of money from Michael Bloomberg recently, so, he has all that -- those initiatives on guns. There are people in the Democratic Party that have certainly benefited from Michael Bloomberg wanting to get involved in politics and he was playing -- he can have a lot of influence on those local races and I think if you look at Virginia this past week on Tuesday, that's just three days ago, he made a big difference there because he was able to get down below on all the noise, focus in, and now Virginia is a blue state.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: And so, just pick up on your point, he put $100 million into the 2018 midterms when the Democrats gained those 40 plus seats.

utterances.speaker: COMPAGNO
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: But I do think, Jesse, that he would say -- a better commercial than the one we just saw from Kamala Harris, he'd say I'm a really real billionaire. That other guy, that Trump guy is a fake billionaire.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Wait a minute. I don't know.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Why did he wait so long? Why did he wait so long?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I don't know. I don't know. I just don't see people in Iowa caucusing from Michael Bloomberg. I just don't see that, all right.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: I get your point. I get your point.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Up next, the left in a frenzy over President Trump heading to a big college football game this weekend.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: It could be another controversial weekend for our president, President Trump. The president headed to a big college football game between Alabama and LSU. The Crimson Tide originally said students would be punished for booing. But after outrage, the school changed its course. NFL legend Terry Bradshaw weighing in earlier today on "Fox and Friends."

utterances.speaker: TERRY BRADSHAW, HOST
utterances.utterance: Hats off to him for having the guts to go in there and do it and I think I'd respect -- you have to simply respect the Office of the President of the United States. It's really right and it's really left and it's angry and it's ugly and it's hostile. I've never seen it like that in this country.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Emily, you can't stop students from booing. That's unconstitutional, ain't it?

utterances.speaker: COMPAGNO
utterances.utterance: Well, that was the point. So the back and forth actually was between the student body president that came out and was basically like you don't boo. And then the actual school came out and said, OK, you have to abide by the capstone creed, essentially, you know, no conduct unbecoming a student and otherwise, of course, you can exercise your First Amendment right against the government or whatever. I just think that silence speaks volumes and to me I was thinking about it like, you know, I was raised in Raider nation like, don't get me wrong. I know how to shout things. But I think if I was sitting in the stands and a president that I didn't agree with came, first of all, I would stand for that office no matter what. And secondly, just don't -- then don't cheer. Just stay quiet, like, can't we just do that.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: So Jesse, you've got to my mind, two schools in red states, Alabama and Louisiana State University. I guess -- it seems to me like a lot of worry. I mean, Trump should be getting a good reception. Is this a sign of some problem?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: No, he's not going to get booed at all, Juan. This is going to get like an overwhelming amount of applause for the president. This is the Deep South. This is MAGA country. The student section is MAGA country. The alumni section, huge amount of Trump support there. I think the initial thing they warned about disruptive behavior, which is like no streaking. Don't do anything crazy to embarrass the school.

utterances.speaker: PEPRINO
utterances.utterance: Oh no, do -- do.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Do you think so?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Right? But I don't think there's going to be any boos.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Did you hear that Jesse?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: What?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Dana says she wants streaking.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I do. I'm the one --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Dana wants streaking?

utterances.speaker: COMPAGNO
utterances.utterance: Here on set, no.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Yes. I do want some drama.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Do you want to see --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: What?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Are you going to watch the game?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I am totally going to watch the game. But here's the thing.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: You think Joe Burrow is going have a good game?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Who?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Quarterback for LSU.

utterances.speaker: COMPAGNO
utterances.utterance: Dana went to little black cat.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I definitely think -- go Tigers, but don't get mad at me if you are from Alabama. I think that the president is exercising excellent political judgment but also it's the benefit of incumbency. He's going to go to the game.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: It's like when Obama went to the NCAA tournament and it's like, oh, that's so cool. He gets to go to that. And if you're the President, you get to go. So, I would definitely go. And also, don't forget, there is a governor's race in Louisiana and that election is next Saturday. President Trump went this week to do a rally to try to help that Republican candidate to try to beat the incumbent Democrat. That's a very close race. I don't know what's going to happen there. But it doesn't hurt that the President is going to this game.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Well, it didn't help in Kentucky, did it?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Not for that particular race, but all the other ones it did.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: I see. So, Greg what do you think about the idea of booing, because you like to boo.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes, I am pro booing. I'm pro cheering. I am pro swearing. This is the news that you get in a golden age.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Right.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Totally.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I mean we're talking about booing and not bombing. You can't spell stock market boom without boo. So, right now CNN is counting the amount of times. Donald Trump says a specific word. He counted 34 times, the static expert on the count that he said, the whistleblower was inaccurate like 34 times. They have people doing that because they don't have any news to report. They go after misspellings. We are in an age - we're in a great age that we're going to look like 10, 20, 30 years from now, we're going to look back. Man, we didn't have any problems when President Kanye West comes in.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Don't get ahead of us. We're coming to that. But you don't think it says anything about his weakness that people in red states are telling the kids don't boo.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I think that this is fake news.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Fake news. You heard that America.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Fake news.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Fake news. All right. That was an original. Rapper Kanye West making major news about his presidential plans. Oh, my goodness. Find out next. When we have the Fastest 7 right here on The Five.

utterances.speaker: COMPAGNO
utterances.utterance: Welcome back. Time for the Fastest 7. First up, are you ready for Kanye 2024. The rapper saying he's ready to run.

utterances.speaker: KANYE WEST, RAPPER
utterances.utterance: When I run for President 2024. We want to definitely - what you're laughing at. When I run for president 2024, we would have created so many jobs that I'm going to walk.

utterances.speaker: COMPAGNO
utterances.utterance: Kanye also saying he could change his name to Christian Genius Billionaire. All right. So, Juan, what do you think about that?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Wait a minute, wait a minute. Christian Genius, wait, he can't mimic Trump. That's not allowed. Look, let me just tell you something. He's not going to run. I don't think so. I mean the moment you declare half the country doesn't like. That's why Oprah and other celebrities don't run. The second point to be made here is when you run, you really have to have a fire in your belly. I mean you really have to want it. You can't just get out there and like how he gave that stare to the audience when they said that. You've got to know. You've got to love - engage the audience. You know Ronald Reagan - when Ronald Reagan ran, it wasn't like he was a celebrity who just ran. Guess what happened, Ronald Reagan was governor of California. He had run for president twice before he ran. So, you've got to put up with all that. I don't see Kanye doing.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: But Juan, this is the same argument that we did against Trump. And I'm one of the people who made that argument. I was just talking about how Reagan did - Reagan was an actor true. But like - and I honestly don't think Trump thought he was going to win when he was going to win. I do believe that Trump has opened the door for Kanye. Persuasion is now more important than politics. I see this wherever I go, like I look at people in a different way, it's like that person could do it. That person can't.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: You think he could?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I think he's a master persuader. He has the art of being memorable and saying the right - I'll put it this way, when Trump got on stage, everybody kind of faded. Imagine him on a stage, don't fade.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: I don't think he's up to--

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: And I have to tell you, Kanye vs Bernie in 2024.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Is that it?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: And the other thing is I admire him for - he has declared himself a Christian. He's done an entire album about it. He is living his faith. And it's not easy to talk about your faith because then you start getting attacked from other people. The other thing I love about it is that he says the new Yeezy sneaker, it's going to be made in Cody, Wyoming and they're moving up there, the headquarters to Cody, Wyoming and I think they'll make great shoes there.

utterances.speaker: COMPAGNO
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I think the secret weapon is Kim Kardashian because that's someone that say they're going to be the First Lady. Think about it. So, Kris Jenner is probably pulling the puppet strings here. She's got this whole thing figured out.

utterances.speaker: COMPAGNO
utterances.utterance: I think it's - he is a phenom. And if he actually does declare, absolutely they will win. Here is why. So, we heard part of his platform already. He talked about an eco-conscious fashion line that he would bring all of his jobs to North America to South America. Think about his commitment through his wife to the criminal justice reform. Think about his messaging for people of color that basically say you're not in mass voting bloc like you are unique. The amount of capital they have between the two of them just on the table alone, $610 million like, anything they put their mind to, they can do.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
